OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1775394664
OL,3,CSuspect found asleep in child-sized
OL,4,Cbed arrested on suspicion of burglary
OL,6,FThey arrived there around 3.15am on
OL,7,F1st April, and found a window had been
OL,8,Fsmashed.
OL,10,FAfter a search of the otherwise empty
OL,11,Fhouse, they found a man sleeping in a
OL,12,Fsmall floor bed in a room full of
OL,13,Fchildren's items.
OL,15,FOfficers woke him up from his sleep,
OL,16,Fand after determining he was not the
OL,17,Fhome-owner, he was put in handcuffs.
OL,19,FThe 24-year-old man was arrested on
OL,20,Fsuspicion of burglary.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/4
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1775394664
OL,3,CSuspect found asleep in child-sized
OL,4,Cbed arrested on suspicion of burglary
OL,6,F"We will always treat incidents of
OL,7,Fthis nature seriously"
OL,9,FInspector Dale Smith from
OL,10,FNottinghamshire Police said:
OL,12,F"The officers responding to this
OL,13,Fincident did a great job apprehending
OL,14,Fa suspect as quickly as they did.
OL,16,F"Having heard a burglary was in
OL,17,Fprogress, the team made their way
OL,18,Fthere and took action when they
OL,19,Fsuspected an intruder could still be
OL,20,Finside the house.
OL,26,@tD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/4
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1775394664
OL,3,CSuspect found asleep in child-sized
OL,4,Cbed arrested on suspicion of burglary
OL,6,F"As it turned out, the property was
OL,7,Fcompletely empty, aside from one man
OL,8,Fwho was lying down on a floor bed in
OL,9,Fone of the rooms.
OL,11,F"As shown by our robust response to
OL,12,Fthis burglary report, we will always
OL,13,Ftreat incidents of this nature
OL,14,Fseriously and act accordingly."
OL,16,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,17,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,18,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,19,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,20,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,21,Fbelow...
